The paper discusses the estimation of mutual information and multi-information in large networks, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also applies these methods to analyze gene expression (cs.SI), financial markets (cs.NE), and consumer preferences (cs.SY), indicating that it could potentially fit under these sub-categories as well.
